./.title: Welcome
./.body:
Hello Elium Students!
Welcome to our living precourse.  We'll be updating this document regularly so be sure to stop by often for bits of humor (we think), helpful tips and fresh study resources.  Feel free to ask for more resources on any topic or let us know if we missed anything!
The best way to succeed is to do a little every day, even just one video!  Check out this motivational article by John Resig himself, the inventor of jQuery.  This website is a great tool for keeping yourself on track.  
Also share your favorite code wars on slack to keep your problem solving sharp.  
Be sure to keep in touch!  
Elium Team

about-course/CurriculumOverview.html.title: Overview
about-course/CurriculumOverview.html.body:
Our curriculum is based on the idea that you learn best by building the most relevant projects.Take a look at gloaysa's repository to see what you'll be making!
The program will have two parts: 
The main curriculum covers three related topics and is designed to bring everyone up to self-sufficiency:

devSkills/.title: Becoming a Developer
devSkills/.body: Writing code is not even half of the gameworking with people and writing good code, that's a big deal

devSkills/goodPractices.html.title: Good Practices
devSkills/goodPractices.html.body:
Some resources for practicing good practices:   

Top 8 Developer Habits - Video series by Mr. Funfunfuncion.      
JS Best Practices - A CLI with exercises that focus on writing good code.  
Javascript Patterns - Advanced, a taste of coming attractions.  
Cleaner, Better Code - 10 tips.  
Be bad at something, it's good for you.

devSkills/gitAndHub.html.title: Git and Github
devSkills/gitAndHub.html.body:

The simple guide to git.  
Derek Banas introduction videos, if you're into that sort of thing.  
The best place to practice git branching.  
I you REALLY want to know how git works.    
Git's documentation.

devSkills/installations.html.title: Installations
devSkills/installations.html.body:
Sublime Text or Atom - Basic text editors that can grow with you.Chrome - Not just a browser, also an indispensible piece of your development environment with it's ChromDev console.Atomic Chrome - This will take a little more time to get used to, but could be worth the effort.Node.js - For running js files in terminal only, don't worry about node servers yet.  
Sublime Linting:  

Sublime Package Control 
Sublime Linter  
jsHint  
ESLint  

visual code seems cool, give it a try too.

jsFounds/.title: Javascript Foundations
jsFounds/.body:
hi.
Javascript is the foundation of everything we'll do here.
Learn your tools!

jsFounds/resources.html.title: Resources
jsFounds/resources.html.body:
resources
* [Simplify Javascript](https://github.com/GeorgeFourikis/Simplify-JavaScript) - a refrence of the examples and concepts Gordon introduces, made for you personally by George.  
* [javascript.info](https://www.javascipt.info) - Somewhere between a text book, a tutorial, and a reference.  The best place to get refer back to through your studies.  
* [The Weird Parts](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bv_5Zv5c-Ts) - A 3 hour video introduction to Javascript.  For those who like videos.
* [videos to accompany FreeCodeCamp](https://medium.freecodecamp.com/my-giant-javascript-basics-course-is-now-live-on-youtube-and-its-100-free-9020a21bbc27)

jsFounds/exercises.html.title: Exercises
jsFounds/exercises.html.body:
exercises
* [FreeCodeCamp](https://www.freecodecamp.com) - A great series of exercises to practice JS language features and solving small problems
* [code wars](codewars.com) - wander your way around here.  Look for codewars that practice what you're having trouble with, or just find fun ones!  The more engaged you are the more you'll learn.  
* [Javascript 30](https://javascript30.com).  30 progressive challenges with accompanying videos.  
* And don't forget "Read, Modify, Create". Search github for projects that interest you and figure out how they made it work.

devProcess/.title: Development Process
devProcess/.body:
Solving CodeWars is the easiest part of writing an application.  
The hardest part is structuring your program and planning your development process.

devProcess/practicalJavascript.html.title: Practical Javascript
devProcess/practicalJavascript.html.body: Practical Javascript - Thorough video series that covers development practices as well as some basics of JS.Complete this video tutorial and push each stage to your github as you finish it.

devProcess/resources.html.title: Resources
devProcess/resources.html.body:
These are some little repos that might help you structure your development process.  
* [From Pseudocode to Code](https://github.com/colevandersWands/banksies/tree/master/part1/english2js)  
* [Simplest Passing Functions] (https://github.com/colevandersWands/banksies/tree/master/part1/simplestPassingFuncs)
